The paper deals with the application of AdaBoost, a popular machine learning algorithm, to cost-sensitive classification problems. The paper presents an empirical study of various approaches proposed in the literature for providing AdaBoost with cost-sensitive properties. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it deals with the application of a machine learning algorithm to a specific problem. It may also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as cost-sensitive classification is a common problem in these fields. Additionally, the paper involves theoretical and empirical analysis, which may lead to classification under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), respectively.
